00:17:56.236 --> 00:17:58.236
approval in treatment-refractory colon cancer.

315
00:17:58.896 --> 00:18:01.996
But then soon thereafter, in 2017, when we began to publish the

316
00:18:02.016 --> 00:18:05.746
tumor responses in non-colon cancer, we received the

317
00:18:05.796 --> 00:18:09.440
first tumor-agnostic concept and FDA approvalSo that concept

318
00:18:09.700 --> 00:18:13.260
didn't exist beforehand, and this was really the first approval that kind of

319
00:18:13.320 --> 00:18:14.760
catapulted this concept into

320
00:18:15.700 --> 00:18:18.000
drug development in a way that hadn't been done before.

321
00:18:18.530 --> 00:18:22.140
But what was interesting is that it no longer looked at the tumor of where it was

322
00:18:22.180 --> 00:18:25.820
born, but it looked at the tumor based on its molecular identity,

323
00:18:26.280 --> 00:18:28.960
and you had a treatment that was approved now based on that.

324
00:18:29.010 --> 00:18:32.550
And so since then, there have been other approvals, both with immune checkpoint

325
00:18:32.600 --> 00:18:36.420
blockade and small molecules that use this tumor-agnostic concept.

326
00:18:38.520 --> 00:18:42.220
So those were advanced tumors, and what I walked you through

327
00:18:42.320 --> 00:18:42.570
was

328
00:18:44.020 --> 00:18:47.810
metastatic tumors that were treatment refractory, PAN tumors, not just

329
00:18:47.810 --> 00:18:51.680
colon cancer. What I didn't show you is now for first-line for many tumor

