341
00:19:31.640 --> 00:19:32.480
tumor resection

342
00:19:33.300 --> 00:19:36.360
or definitive chemotherapy, radiation, or in some cases,

343
00:19:36.400 --> 00:19:40.370
immunotherapy. The tumor's removed, and you have no idea

344
00:19:40.420 --> 00:19:42.850
if your patient's cured or not. No idea.

345
00:19:44.160 --> 00:19:47.940
And you have to wait to see if the tumor's going to recur or not.

346
00:19:47.980 --> 00:19:50.230
There are some risk stratifiers, but they're all not very good.

347
00:19:50.920 --> 00:19:54.820
So the concept was, is there a way to measure something immediately after surgery

348
00:19:55.580 --> 00:19:57.740
that could define someone as cured or not cured?

349
00:19:59.120 --> 00:20:02.820
And the idea for this started in about 2007.

350
00:20:03.020 --> 00:20:05.040
This is one of our graduate students, Carlo Rago,

351
00:20:06.500 --> 00:20:10.260
where we were first looking at fragments of DNA, or we were looking for a way to

