00:21:40.400 --> 00:21:44.330
flow cytometry. And you see the wild-type fragments in green and

382
00:21:44.360 --> 00:21:45.560
the mutant fragments there in red.

383
00:21:46.240 --> 00:21:49.540
And you see after a curative resection, day one, day 42, and day

384
00:21:49.660 --> 00:21:50.300
244.

385
00:21:51.160 --> 00:21:54.420
And at day one, you see the mutant fragments almost disappear.

386
00:21:55.960 --> 00:21:59.360
And at day 42, the CT scan's negative when they see the medical

387
00:21:59.380 --> 00:22:03.159
oncologist, but then the patient recurs at day 244, and you see the

388
00:22:03.200 --> 00:22:04.379
mutant fragments have increased.

389
00:22:06.300 --> 00:22:09.360
And so what we were seeing here is the evolution of minimal residual disease.

390
00:22:09.480 --> 00:22:12.150
It's not visible by the surgeon, not visible by radiology,

391
00:22:13.220 --> 00:22:17.200
not detectable by any other methodology, but we were able to track

392
00:22:17.220 --> 00:22:21.100
the tumor recurrence very early. Now, the half-life of these

393
00:22:21.140 --> 00:22:24.260
fragments is two hours. That was measured at 24 hours.

394
00:22:24.599 --> 00:22:26.500
There should be no circulating tumor DNA at 24 hours.

395
00:22:26.880 --> 00:22:29.080
We knew at day one that patient was going to recur.

396
00:22:29.360 --> 00:22:33.340
There was residual disease because what creates this is cells that

397
00:22:33.380 --> 00:22:36.060
are constantly turning over, or cancer cells in the body.

398
00:22:37.330 --> 00:22:40.910
And when we looked at a large number of patients, or a small number of patients,

399
00:22:41.000 --> 00:22:44.840
but in the larger number of patients, we saw those with detectable ctDNA all

400
00:22:44.880 --> 00:22:47.740
recurred, and those with undetectable ctDNA did not recur.

401
00:22:48.460 --> 00:22:52.440
So for us, setting up the concept of minimal residual disease

402
00:22:52.880 --> 00:22:54.260
defined by circulating tumor DNA.

403
00:22:54.300 --> 00:22:57.880
So defining who's cured and who's not cured immediately after surgery.

404
00:22:59.200 --> 00:22:59.560
And so

405
00:23:00.800 --> 00:23:04.100
since that paper was published, and it's taken a long time, there's probably been

406
00:23:04.760 --> 00:23:08.460
50 to 100 patients, papers published using minimal

407
00:23:08.480 --> 00:23:11.799
residual disease measured by ctDNA to prognosticate

