00:23:12.240 --> 00:23:15.580
recurrence or not recurrence after surgery in virtually every tumor type.

409
00:23:16.090 --> 00:23:19.220
And what we know is that if you're circulating tumor DNA positive after surgery,

410
00:23:19.660 --> 00:23:22.160
the likelihood you're going to recur is in 90%.

411
00:23:23.320 --> 00:23:24.680
It's not as good as if you're negative.

412
00:23:24.830 --> 00:23:27.100
If you're negative, the likelihood that you won't recur

413
00:23:28.180 --> 00:23:30.280
is still not very predictive.

414
00:23:31.260 --> 00:23:35.000
But the reason I brought this up in this talk about immunotherapy is because we

415
00:23:35.040 --> 00:23:36.740
wanted to bring this concept forward

416
00:23:37.660 --> 00:23:40.920
in looking at the effectiveness of mismatched paired blockade in the minimal

417
00:23:41.120 --> 00:23:42.120
residual disease setting

418
00:23:42.920 --> 00:23:46.500
and combine that with the predictive value of circulating tumor DNA in

419
00:23:46.600 --> 00:23:48.080
minimal residual disease.

420
00:23:49.040 --> 00:23:50.280
And so the questions were

421
00:23:51.180 --> 00:23:54.740
can an intervention with PD-1 blockade tumors eradicate minimal residual disease

422
00:23:55.080 --> 00:23:58.880
detected by ctDNA? And two, could you alter the

423
00:23:58.960 --> 00:24:02.660
natural history of disease? Since you're positive after surgery you're going to

424
00:24:02.700 --> 00:24:04.860
recur, can we alter that natural history?

425
00:24:05.960 --> 00:24:09.160
And so we conceived it with Yelena Janjigian,

426
00:24:10.280 --> 00:24:12.120
and this is not an easy study.

427
00:24:13.460 --> 00:24:17.452
And you've got to beA workhorse to get a study like

428
00:24:17.492 --> 00:24:21.412
this done. And so we took patients that underwent an

429
00:24:21.552 --> 00:24:24.152
R0 surgical resection. That means clean margins.

