00:26:07.052 --> 00:26:09.432
25 were positive and 125 were negative.

464
00:26:10.272 --> 00:26:13.372
So I'm going to start with the negative patients. What do you think they look like?

465
00:26:14.932 --> 00:26:17.272
They were negative and just observed. They did quite well.

466
00:26:17.552 --> 00:26:18.152
Not perfect,

467
00:26:19.212 --> 00:26:23.032
and newer assays, that curve would be better, but it wasn't

468
00:26:23.072 --> 00:26:24.672
perfect, right? So some patients recurred.

469
00:26:25.752 --> 00:26:29.132
What if you were ctDNA positive, because we had some, and they did not receive

470
00:26:29.172 --> 00:26:29.812
anti-PD-1?

471
00:26:31.572 --> 00:26:34.252
They did super poorly, and they progressed quite rapidly.

472
00:26:35.732 --> 00:26:38.172
What if you were ctDNA positive and you received anti-PD-1?

473
00:26:39.932 --> 00:26:43.872
So it was closer to the patients who were ctDNA

474
00:26:43.912 --> 00:26:46.812
negative and just observed. And so a couple of things.

475
00:26:46.932 --> 00:26:49.212
So these patients were treated for six months.

476
00:26:50.252 --> 00:26:53.172
I think a longer duration of treatment would see a better response.

477
00:26:54.072 --> 00:26:57.501
And I think that a better assay would actually probably find patients slightly

